01:19:31.167 --> 01:19:31.887
two He's,

01:19:31.948 --> 01:19:33.710
observant individuals in Yahowah's name,

01:19:34.109 --> 01:19:34.990
is also included.

01:19:35.591 --> 01:19:35.912
Further,

01:19:35.952 --> 01:19:38.033
when we follow Dowd through the

01:19:38.073 --> 01:19:40.416
invitations to be called out and meet with

01:19:40.496 --> 01:19:40.856
God,

01:19:41.296 --> 01:19:44.579
we pass through the same door on Pesach

01:19:45.119 --> 01:19:49.083
and are anointed with the same spirit on

01:19:49.203 --> 01:19:49.703
Matsah,

01:19:50.024 --> 01:19:51.765
such that we too become part of the

01:19:51.826 --> 01:19:53.587
covenant family on Bikuwrym.

01:19:54.148 --> 01:19:55.969
It's on Matsah that he removes our

01:19:56.090 --> 01:20:00.033
political and religious guilt,

01:20:00.073 --> 01:20:01.054
taking it off to Sheowl.

01:20:03.581 --> 01:20:05.521
So as we contemplate what comes next,

01:20:06.643 --> 01:20:08.864
we're reminded that Yahowah works through

01:20:08.904 --> 01:20:12.487
men and women who are surprisingly similar

01:20:12.527 --> 01:20:12.967
to us.

01:20:13.847 --> 01:20:17.570
And the ones that he prefers and uses

01:20:18.011 --> 01:20:20.332
over and over again are those who are

01:20:20.393 --> 01:20:23.515
also surprisingly similar to him.

01:20:25.457 --> 01:20:27.699
Now, for example, Shamul was a good man,

01:20:27.920 --> 01:20:29.501
a man of character and conscience,

01:20:29.561 --> 01:20:33.244
but when acting on his own initiative and

01:20:33.265 --> 01:20:35.086
apart from divine inspiration,

01:20:35.546 --> 01:20:38.349
he was as susceptible to jumping to errant

01:20:38.389 --> 01:20:40.570
conclusions as the rest of us.

01:20:41.551 --> 01:20:45.194
Even Yahowah's prophets, the judges even,

01:20:45.295 --> 01:20:46.395
experts in the Towrah,

01:20:46.975 --> 01:20:50.760
those who had personal conversations with

01:20:50.779 --> 01:20:51.140
Yahowah,

01:20:52.264 --> 01:20:53.784
are not only capable of error,

01:20:54.206 --> 01:20:56.287
it's an essential aspect of who we are.

01:20:56.426 --> 01:20:59.449
It's these errors that we have to learn

01:20:59.489 --> 01:21:01.511
from and overcome that is the only way

01:21:01.551 --> 01:21:04.814
for us to demonstrate that we are doing

01:21:04.854 --> 01:21:06.855
what we should be doing, learning,

01:21:06.876 --> 01:21:09.778
growing, improving, correcting,

01:21:10.798 --> 01:21:12.159
getting up when we trip and fall,

01:21:12.600 --> 01:21:13.981
proving that we can be trusted.

01:21:15.002 --> 01:21:15.882
So it's one of the things that I

01:21:15.922 --> 01:21:18.265
find so appealing and genuine

01:21:19.554 --> 01:21:21.916
about those that Yahowah has chosen to

01:21:21.956 --> 01:21:22.536
represent him.

01:21:23.056 --> 01:21:25.439
We not only don't have to be perfect,

01:21:26.139 --> 01:21:27.460
we will never be perfect.

01:21:27.640 --> 01:21:29.141
And even God's not perfect,

01:21:29.601 --> 01:21:30.603
nor does he want to be,

01:21:30.682 --> 01:21:32.163
nor does he want us to be perfect

01:21:32.184 --> 01:21:32.845
because we are perfect.

01:21:32.864 --> 01:21:34.206
There'd be nothing to achieve,

01:21:35.226 --> 01:21:36.448
nothing that could be accomplished,

01:21:36.627 --> 01:21:37.528
nowhere to grow,

01:21:38.189 --> 01:21:42.332
nothing to differentiate one from another.

01:21:42.492 --> 01:21:44.993
And it could never demonstrate that we can

01:21:45.033 --> 01:21:45.435
be trusted.

01:21:45.454 --> 01:21:46.154
We can never learn.

01:21:46.175 --> 01:21:47.997
We could never be anything more than we

01:21:48.016 --> 01:21:48.157
were

01:21:48.716 --> 01:21:49.436
conceived to be.

01:21:49.476 --> 01:21:54.661
What a waste of eternity.

01:21:54.680 --> 01:21:57.823
God wants us to be receptive to him,

01:21:58.622 --> 01:21:59.884
to go where his words lead.

01:22:00.583 --> 01:22:01.265
And in this case,

01:22:01.305 --> 01:22:06.368
they lead past the first seven sons to

01:22:06.387 --> 01:22:09.248
the eighth symbolic, of course,

01:22:09.288 --> 01:22:10.149
of eternal life.

01:22:13.956 --> 01:22:16.518
And it came to exist when they arrived

01:22:16.557 --> 01:22:19.020
and they saw Ely'ab.

01:22:19.640 --> 01:22:21.722
Ely'ab is my God is father.

01:22:22.722 --> 01:22:23.783
My father is God.

01:22:24.925 --> 01:22:25.426
And said,

01:22:25.985 --> 01:22:29.569
surely Yahowah's anointing of him will be

01:22:29.628 --> 01:22:31.911
straightaway and conspicuous.

01:22:32.992 --> 01:22:34.552
Straightaway and conspicuous from the get.

01:22:34.592 --> 01:22:36.654
It's a term very, very,

01:22:36.814 --> 01:22:38.737
very often applied to Dowd that

01:22:39.278 --> 01:22:41.359
that Dowd was Yahowah's counterpart.

01:22:41.738 --> 01:22:44.399
He was conspicuous counterpart of Yahowah

01:22:44.420 --> 01:22:46.480
because the personalities were so similar.

01:22:47.440 --> 01:22:50.942
However, Yahowah declared to Shamuw’el,

01:22:51.322 --> 01:22:55.024
do not focus upon or have regard for

01:22:55.064 --> 01:22:56.104
his appearance.

01:22:56.783 --> 01:22:57.944
Stop looking at the body.

01:22:59.206 --> 01:22:59.666
God,

01:22:59.826 --> 01:23:01.307
it's the whole thing I'm trying to

01:23:01.448 --> 01:23:03.769
emphasize with our covenant family to

01:23:03.809 --> 01:23:05.149
prepare you for what's coming.

01:23:05.570 --> 01:23:09.194
Stop looking at physical appearances.

01:23:09.713 --> 01:23:11.414
It's the soul that matters.

01:23:12.395 --> 01:23:15.037
Is that soul reliable?

01:23:15.257 --> 01:23:17.479
Is that soul aggressive?

01:23:17.939 --> 01:23:21.662
Is that soul focused and dedicated on

01:23:21.743 --> 01:23:22.143
learning?

01:23:22.283 --> 01:23:24.385
Is that soul committed to

01:23:25.408 --> 01:23:28.449
Is that soul one that you can rely

01:23:28.489 --> 01:23:31.692
upon to not give up and get this

01:23:31.771 --> 01:23:32.612
job done?

01:23:33.592 --> 01:23:39.076
Is that soul inquisitive?

01:23:39.155 --> 01:23:42.837
Focus on the soul and not the body,

01:23:42.938 --> 01:23:45.679
and you won't have a tough time trying

01:23:45.698 --> 01:23:48.461
to understand why God redeploys certain

01:23:48.520 --> 01:23:48.881
souls.

01:23:51.894 --> 01:23:54.296
and don't regard his stature and height.

01:23:54.315 --> 01:23:55.256
Oh, good.

01:23:55.337 --> 01:23:55.936
Yeah, of course,

01:23:55.997 --> 01:23:58.498
everybody would like to be six foot,

01:23:59.100 --> 01:24:02.162
you know, or more, six foot four and,

01:24:02.702 --> 01:24:02.983
you know,

01:24:03.063 --> 01:24:06.085
chiseled and tower over other men.

01:24:06.145 --> 01:24:07.365
And he says, stop that.

01:24:07.525 --> 01:24:09.507
I mean, Dowd was probably five foot eight.

01:24:10.828 --> 01:24:13.230
My guess is maybe five foot ten at

01:24:13.291 --> 01:24:13.610
most.

01:24:14.572 --> 01:24:16.372
Stop looking at stature.

01:24:17.573 --> 01:24:20.055
Stop looking at physical appearances.

01:24:23.246 --> 01:24:25.127
If I can convince you to do that

01:24:26.148 --> 01:24:28.970
and to recognize that Yahowah values souls

01:24:28.989 --> 01:24:31.971
that have attributes and attitudes,

01:24:32.853 --> 01:24:34.914
personality and experiences,

01:24:35.494 --> 01:24:38.577
a will to succeed and be steadfast and

01:24:38.697 --> 01:24:39.238
overcome,

01:24:40.538 --> 01:24:43.020
then I will have taken you to where

01:24:43.121 --> 01:24:43.381
I am.

01:24:45.502 --> 01:24:45.943
It says,

01:24:46.143 --> 01:24:47.984
don't look at these things because I have

01:24:48.024 --> 01:24:48.645
rejected him.

01:24:49.786 --> 01:24:50.605
That's not impressed.

01:24:52.488 --> 01:24:53.028
For indeed,

01:24:54.579 --> 01:24:58.405
inconsistent with the way that man views

01:24:58.445 --> 01:24:59.287
humankind,

01:25:00.127 --> 01:25:02.411
considering an individual's visual

01:25:02.572 --> 01:25:03.372
appearance.

01:25:04.493 --> 01:25:05.194
But instead,

01:25:05.234 --> 01:25:09.100
Yahowah perceives a person's character and

01:25:09.400 --> 01:25:10.082
conscience

01:25:11.177 --> 01:25:12.859
la ha lebab

01:25:13.578 --> 01:25:16.381
the inclination to exercise good judgment.

01:25:16.440 --> 01:25:18.341
The heart was the seat of judgment,

01:25:18.721 --> 01:25:20.662
of thinking, of thoughts, of choices,

01:25:20.722 --> 01:25:22.823
of volition, of the mind and heart,

01:25:22.863 --> 01:25:25.685
of the ability to distinguish between

01:25:25.805 --> 01:25:26.646
right and wrong,

01:25:26.987 --> 01:25:29.047
the conviction to see it through.

01:25:29.828 --> 01:25:32.810
Courage, character.

01:25:32.850 --> 01:25:34.070
That's what Yahowah says.

01:25:34.730 --> 01:25:36.011
Samuel, listen to him.

01:25:36.051 --> 01:25:38.092
First Samuel, six, ten, seven.

01:25:39.095 --> 01:25:40.296
And that is where we're going to lead

01:25:40.497 --> 01:25:41.436
this program,

01:25:41.737 --> 01:25:43.238
because I want you to think about that.

01:25:43.719 --> 01:25:44.238
God says,

01:25:44.798 --> 01:25:48.180
I do not look at physical appearances.

01:25:48.520 --> 01:25:50.481
They mean nothing to me.

01:25:51.743 --> 01:25:54.363
I don't care about his height,

01:25:54.604 --> 01:25:57.386
his stature, his personal presence,

01:25:57.445 --> 01:25:59.707
his self-image,

01:26:00.847 --> 01:26:03.929
or any part of his visual appearance of

01:26:03.969 --> 01:26:06.631
what can be seen with the eyes.

01:26:09.144 --> 01:26:09.663
No,

01:26:10.425 --> 01:26:14.889
I'm interested in what makes him special.

01:26:16.829 --> 01:26:18.371
Not in his visual appearance,

01:26:18.771 --> 01:26:24.355
but in his le baba, his character,

01:26:25.837 --> 01:26:26.698
his conscience,

01:26:27.958 --> 01:26:33.342
his inclination to exercise good judgment,

01:26:33.403 --> 01:26:35.305
his thinking, his thoughts, his choices,

01:26:35.364 --> 01:26:35.524
his

01:26:37.694 --> 01:26:38.194
Volition.

01:26:38.934 --> 01:26:39.914
Mind and heart.

01:26:43.796 --> 01:26:44.796
That's what matters to God.

01:26:46.396 --> 01:26:47.537
And quite frankly,

01:26:47.858 --> 01:26:49.257
that doesn't sound like a very high

01:26:49.337 --> 01:26:49.819
standard.

01:26:51.738 --> 01:26:53.680
There have been exceedingly few people

01:26:53.699 --> 01:26:55.520
that have measured up.

01:26:56.301 --> 01:26:59.282
And of those who have actually reached the

01:26:59.322 --> 01:27:02.203
point where God says, I like that person.

01:27:02.563 --> 01:27:03.363
That's my guy.

01:27:03.884 --> 01:27:05.765
Like Chanowk, Enoch.

01:27:05.784 --> 01:27:05.864
Like

01:27:08.845 --> 01:27:14.908
EliYah, like Dowd, and like some others.

01:27:17.088 --> 01:27:20.610
They are rare indeed.

01:27:20.791 --> 01:27:23.492
And if we're going to appreciate what God

01:27:23.532 --> 01:27:24.271
appreciates,

01:27:26.233 --> 01:27:27.653
we need to appreciate them too.

01:27:29.094 --> 01:27:30.054
Well, I thank you for listening.

01:27:30.134 --> 01:27:31.534
We endured the wind.

01:27:31.595 --> 01:27:33.234
I hope the howl wasn't too much in

01:27:33.255 --> 01:27:34.176
the microphone.

01:27:34.216 --> 01:27:36.417
This happens to be a jewel that...

01:27:37.935 --> 01:27:39.775
Rich actually acquired for us.

01:27:39.796 --> 01:27:42.438
This is the top end of the shore

01:27:42.537 --> 01:27:42.818
line.

01:27:42.858 --> 01:27:46.180
He is a microphone aficionado,

01:27:46.380 --> 01:27:49.001
and he picked this one and this particular

01:27:49.360 --> 01:27:51.762
sock that goes over it just so that

01:27:51.802 --> 01:27:54.043
we could do programs on blustery days out

01:27:54.083 --> 01:27:57.126
here in our ocean studio because we love

01:27:57.166 --> 01:27:57.805
the environment.

01:27:57.826 --> 01:27:59.067
We think it's, well,

01:27:59.127 --> 01:28:01.688
it's an invocative of the role we're

01:28:01.728 --> 01:28:02.047
playing.

01:28:02.127 --> 01:28:04.189
It's the man from the sea who embraces

01:28:04.229 --> 01:28:04.710
the land.

01:28:05.990 --> 01:28:07.492
So here we are above the sea,

01:28:08.853 --> 01:28:14.998
and it's just so open and exposed that

01:28:15.019 --> 01:28:19.042
you're able to see the character and

01:28:19.082 --> 01:28:21.925
conscience of the person speaking to you,

01:28:22.246 --> 01:28:24.488
who cares enough to tell you what they

01:28:24.507 --> 01:28:27.350
have learned from being in God's presence.

01:28:28.390 --> 01:28:29.932
Thank you for listening.

01:28:29.953 --> 01:28:30.252
Good day.

01:28:33.837 --> 01:28:35.461
Hey there, thanks for tuning in.

